# AIOS — AURA OS

**Adaptive User-space Runtime Architecture** — a fully portable, modular, offline-first OS-like layer that runs on top of any host (Termux/Android, Linux, macOS, Windows, Docker) and dynamically reconfigures itself based on available capabilities.

---

## Features

| Capability | Description |
|---|---|
| 🔍 **Environment detection** | Auto-detects Android/Termux, Linux, macOS, Windows, WSL, RAM, binaries, network |
| 🔌 **EAL adapters** | Unified file/process/network API per platform (`android`, `linux`, `macos`, `windows`, `fallback`) |
| 🤖 **Offline AI** | Rule-based assistant with optional GGUF model (llama-cpp-python) |
| 🖥️ **Dual UI** | Flask web dashboard (port 7070) with terminal fallback |
| 📁 **File system manager** | `ls`, `cat`, `find`, `mkdir`, `rm`, `edit` via EAL |
| 📦 **Repo manager** | `git init`, `commit`, `status`, `clone` via EAL |
| ⚙️ **Automation engine** | JSON task workflows with `run`, `log`, `sleep`, `write` steps |
| 🚀 **Bootstrap** | One-shot install + Termux:Boot / systemd integration |
| 🐳 **Docker** | Run anywhere with `docker build -t aura . && docker run aura` |

---

## Directory Structure

```
AIOS/
├── aura                   ← CLI entry point (Unix/macOS)
├── aura.cmd               ← CLI entry point (Windows)
├── install.sh             ← Master installation script
├── pyproject.toml         ← Python packaging (pip install .)
├── Dockerfile             ← Container deployment
├── boot/
│   └── startup.py         ← Bootstrap & initialisation
├── aura_os/               ← Main Python package
│   ├── __main__.py        ← python -m aura_os support
│   ├── main.py            ← CLI entry & interactive shell
│   ├── eal/               ← Environment Abstraction Layer
│   │   ├── detector.py    ← Platform detection
│   │   └── adapters/
│   │       ├── android.py ← Termux/Android adapter
│   │       ├── linux.py   ← Linux adapter
│   │       ├── macos.py   ← macOS adapter
│   │       ├── windows.py ← Windows adapter
│   │       └── fallback.py← Unknown platform adapter
│   ├── engine/            ← Command routing & dispatch
│   ├── kernel/            ← Syslog, process, service mgmt
│   ├── fs/                ← Virtual filesystem
│   ├── pkg/               ← Package management
│   └── ai/                ← AI inference & knowledge
├── modules/               ← Plugin-style modules
├── configs/
│   └── system.json        ← Default configuration
├── tests/                 ← 200+ unit tests
└── .github/workflows/
    └── ci.yml             ← CI on Linux, macOS, Windows
```

---

## Installation

### pip install (recommended — all platforms)

```bash
pip install .
aura --help
```

Or install with optional extras:

```bash
pip install ".[ai,web,shell,dev]"
```

### Quick Install (shell script)

```bash
bash install.sh
```

The script will:
1. Detect your environment (Termux, apt, dnf, pacman, brew, WSL, …)
2. Verify Python 3.8+ is available
3. Create `~/.aura/` runtime directory
4. Add `~/.aura/bin` to your shell profile
5. Set up Termux:Boot integration (Android only)

### Termux (Android)

```bash
pkg install git python
git clone https://github.com/Cbetts1/AIOS.git
cd AIOS
pip install .
```

### Linux / macOS

```bash
git clone https://github.com/Cbetts1/AIOS.git
cd AIOS
pip install .
```

### Windows

```powershell
git clone https://github.com/Cbetts1/AIOS.git
cd AIOS
pip install .
```

Or use the batch script directly: `aura.cmd --help`

### Docker

```bash
docker build -t aura-os .
docker run --rm aura-os --help
docker run --rm -it aura-os shell
```

### Manual (no install)

```bash
export AURA_HOME=~/.aura
python3 -m aura_os --help
```

---

## Commands

```
aura help                  Show all commands
aura sys info              System information
aura sys caps              Detected capabilities
aura env                   Full environment JSON
aura reload                Re-detect environment

aura run <file>            Run .py / .sh / .js file
aura ai "<prompt>"         Offline AI assistant
aura fs ls [path]          List files/directories
aura fs cat <file>         Print file contents
aura fs find [path] [pat]  Search for files
aura fs mkdir <path>       Create directory
aura fs rm <path>          Delete file or directory
aura fs edit <file>        Open in text editor

aura repo create <name>    Init a new git repo
aura repo list             List managed repos
aura repo status [path]    Show git status
aura repo clone <url>      Clone remote repo (needs network)

aura auto list             List automation tasks
aura auto create <name>    Create a task template
aura auto run <name>       Execute a task

aura ui                    Auto-select UI (web or terminal)
aura ui web                Launch web UI (http://localhost:7070)
aura ui term               Launch terminal dashboard
```

---

## Example Workflows

### Run a script

```bash
aura run myscript.py
aura run deploy.sh
```

### Ask the AI assistant

```bash
aura ai "how do I create a git repo"
aura ai "write a python function to read a csv"
aura ai "what commands are available"
```

### Manage repositories

```bash
aura repo create myapp
aura repo list
aura repo status myapp
```

### Automation

```bash
aura auto create deploy
# Edit ~/.aura/tasks/deploy.json
aura auto run deploy
```

### Web UI

```bash
aura ui web
# Open http://localhost:7070 in your browser
```

---

## Using a Local AI Model

AURA uses a rule-based fallback by default. To enable a real local LLM:

1. Install llama-cpp-python:
   ```bash
   pip install llama-cpp-python
   ```
2. Place a `.gguf` model file in `~/.aura/models/` (e.g. `tinyllama.gguf`)
3. Run any `aura ai` command — the model is auto-detected

Recommended small models:
- TinyLlama 1.1B (≈600 MB): works on most devices including Android
- Phi-2 (≈1.7 GB): better quality, requires ≥2 GB RAM

---

## Adaptation Logic

At startup, AURA builds a **capability map**:

```json
{
  "env_type": "linux",
  "is_termux": false,
  "capabilities": ["python", "git", "node", "flask", "web_ui", "heavy_modules"],
  "ram_mb": 8192,
  "has_network": false
}
```

Modules are then selected dynamically:

| Condition | Behaviour |
|---|---|
| `flask` in caps | Enable web UI |
| `flask` absent | Fall back to terminal dashboard |
| `git` in caps | Enable repo module |
| `ram_mb < 512` | Disable heavy modules |
| `is_termux` | Use pkg / Termux:Boot |
| No network | Operate fully offline |

---

## Running Tests

```bash
pip install ".[dev]"
python -m pytest tests/ -v
```

200+ tests covering EAL detection, adapters, command engine, all modules, kernel, filesystem, and more.

---

## Architecture

```
CLI (aura / python -m aura_os)
    │
    ▼
CommandRouter ──► CommandHandlers
    │
    ├──► EAL (detector → adapter)
    │        ├── AndroidAdapter  (Termux)
    │        ├── LinuxAdapter    (Linux)
    │        ├── MacOSAdapter    (macOS)
    │        ├── WindowsAdapter  (Windows)
    │        └── FallbackAdapter (unknown)
    │
    ├──► aura_os/ai         (offline AI assistant)
    ├──► aura_os/kernel     (syslog, process, service mgmt)
    ├──► aura_os/fs         (virtual filesystem)
    ├──► aura_os/pkg        (package management)
    └──► modules/           (plugins: browser, repo, automation)
```
